Talisman

Purpose:
- Conflict handling, no-op behavior, and protected-anchor change-control guidance for the MemoryEndpoints.com active memory suite.

Verification status: active operational memory; verify with `.uai/memory-maintenance.uai` and current human instructions before relying on it.
Memory scope: anchor governance, contradiction handling, review routing, and no-op behavior.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: change this file only when a human names this exact artifact and exact operation; record the reason in `.uai/decisions.uai`.
Source of truth: `.uai/totem.uai`, `.uai/taboo.uai`, `.uai/memory-maintenance.uai`, and current human instructions.
Next action for agents: when memory conflicts, preserve safety, name the conflict, and update the responsible typed file only after resolving authority.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, raw one-time keys, or unredacted private evidence.

Conflict rules:
- Human instructions beat generated memory when they are explicit and safe.
- Current code, tests, and fresh reports beat stale summaries.
- Totem preserves the positive invariant: local `.uai` stays active always.
- Taboo preserves hard boundaries and forbidden claims.
- If an anchor appears stale, harmful, contradictory, malformed, or missing, no-op on the risky action and report the exact issue instead of silently rewriting the anchor.
- Durable MATM memory can augment and search history, but it does not silently supersede this active suite.
